==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fenestration
<hw>Fen`es*tra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The arrangement and proportioning of windows; --
used by modern writers for the decorating of an architectural
composition by means of the window (and door) openings, their ornaments,
and proportions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The state or condition of being
fenestrated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fenestrule</ent>⟦br⟧
